==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gambit
<hw>Gam"bit</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>gambit</ets>,
cf. It. <ets>gambitto</ets> gambit, a tripping up. See <er>Gambol</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <fld>(Chess Playing)</fld> <def>A mode of opening
the game, in which a pawn is sacrificed to gain an attacking
position.</def> <-- Hence, Fig. any stratagem; in conversation, a
remark, often prepared in advance, calculated to provoke discussion,
amuse, or make a point = a conversational gambit --> ⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gamble</ent>⟦br⟧
